# File Naming Conventions

> **Seven-layer week bundles (this repo)**: See [09_week-companion-architecture.mdc](./09_week-companion-architecture.mdc) for the week reference table, on-demand creation, learning flow, and migration SOP.

## Topic / week numbering

- **Start at `01_`**: Week/topic numbering starts at `01_` (no `00_`).
- **Sequential**: Use `01_` … `08_` for the Term 1 course map in rule `09` (extend with `09_`+ only if the curriculum adds more weeks).

## Week-based naming (`weeks/weekN/`)

All eight weeks use `weeks/weekN/` folders with step-numbered filenames. The folder name provides the week context.

| Step | Filename | Layer |
|------|----------|-------|
| 01 | `01_reading-notes.md` | Theory — concepts, definitions, intuition (first-person voice) |
| 02 | `02_examples.md` | Practice — worked examples (original scenarios) |
| 03 | `03_quiz.md` | Self-assessment (original synthesis only; one per week default) |
| 04 | `04_notebook.ipynb` | Experiments — hands-on preprocessing and visualizations |
| 05 | `05_model-paper.md` | Model papers — exam-style readiness (answers in-file or paired file) |
| 06 | `06_discussion.md` | Discussion — reflection / forum prompts for the same week |
| 07 | `07_assignment.md` | Assignment — structured weekly deliverables |

**Trimester-level extras in `weeks/`:**

- `weeks/assignments/` — Graded assignment (FIFA21 + Laptop datasets)
- `weeks/model-papers/` — 5 comprehensive exam papers covering all 8 weeks + consolidated answers guide

## Python scripts (`src/`)

- Use **snake_case** (standard Python).
- **No** `XX_` topic prefix required — this is utility/library code, not a learning layer.

## Images & figures

- Descriptive kebab-case (e.g. `missing-values-plot.png`).

## Tools (`tools/`)

- Scripts and helpers only; not part of the seven learning layers.
